onyomiExamples.meaning: waxing and waning, phases of moon
waxing and waning of the moon, phase of the moon, rising and falling (of fortune)
waning and waxing (usu. of the moon)

kunyomiExamples.meaning: to fill, to become full (of), to be filled (with), to brim (with), to wax (of the moon), to rise (of the tide), to flow, to come in, to expire (of a period of time), to mature, to come to an end
